<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="497" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Fox</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-02"><hi rend="italic">June 2,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The following telegram has been received from the legation at Lima
                            (supra, June 1):</p>
                        <p>Hasten solemnly to impress the Government of Ecuador with the fact that
                            by failure to take similar action and to make their acceptance
                            unencumbered with premature arguments they would assume before the world
                            the responsibility of jeopardizing the mediation and of the grave
                            consequences which might follow.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>